    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">ROI Examples for Swansea Businesses</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Abstract pricing means nothing without concrete outcomes. Here are two real-world scenarios showing what SEO investment delivers for Swansea businesses.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Mumbles Restaurant: 50 Extra Covers Per Month</h3>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A seafood restaurant on Mumbles Road was relying entirely on walk-ins and TripAdvisor. They had no Google Business Profile optimisation and their website ranked on page three for "restaurant Mumbles" and "seafood Swansea." On the Starter plan at £497 per month, we optimised their Google Business Profile, built local citations, and targeted five high-intent keywords including "best restaurant Mumbles" and "seafood restaurant Swansea Bay."</p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Within four months, they ranked in the local map pack for all five keywords. Online reservations increased by 50 covers per month, worth approximately £1,250 in additional revenue at an average £25 per head. That is a 2.5x return on a £497 monthly investment, and the results compound as domain authority grows.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-3">Morriston Trades Business: 20 New Leads Per Month</h3>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A plumbing and heating company based near <strong>Morriston Hospital</strong> was spending £800 per month on Google Ads with inconsistent results. They switched to the Growth plan at £997 per month. We targeted 15 keywords covering emergency plumbing, boiler installation, and heating services across Swansea postcodes. We also built out location-specific service pages for areas including <strong>SA1 Waterfront</strong>, Sketty, Uplands, and Gorseinon.</p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">By month five, organic traffic had increased by 340%. The business now receives an average of 20 qualified leads per month through organic search, each worth between £150 and £3,000 depending on the job. Even at a conservative average job value of £500 with a 30% close rate, that is £3,000 per month in new revenue from a £997 investment. Unlike paid ads, these rankings continue to deliver leads without ongoing click costs.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Swansea vs Cardiff vs Bristol: SEO Pricing Comparison</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Swansea businesses benefit from a pricing advantage that Cardiff and Bristol companies do not have. Here is how typical monthly SEO retainers compare across the three cities.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
